-- Chile Stocks: Azul Azul, Endesa and Sigdo Koppers
-- B y   S e b a s t i a n   B o y d   a n d   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-06-28T12:36:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-26/chile-stocks-azul-azul-endesa-and-sigdo-koppers-are-active.html
(Corrects company name in fourth paragraph of story
originally published on June 26.)  The following companies had  unusual 
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close in Santiago.  The  Ipsa index  fell 0.1 percent to 4,324.01. The  MSCI Chile
index (MXCL)  retreated 0.2 percent to 2,315.31.  Azul Azul SA (AZUL)  , the owner of the Universidad de
 Chile  soccer team, jumped 13 percent to 1,865.2 pesos after La
Tercera reported that the company stood to earn $2 million from
the trade of Junior Fernandes to Bayer 04 Leverkusen. The stock
exchange asked for an explanation after the shares earlier
reached 1,950 pesos, according to a statement on the exchange’s
website. Azul Azul advanced 18 percent yesterday after the team
defeated Santiago-based Colo Colo to move to the finals of the
Chilean  soccer tournament .  Sigdo Koppers SA (SK)   gained 1.4 percent to 1,189 pesos
after Chile’s government said in an e-mailed statement that the
industrial holding company will sign a $900 million agreement
with  China ’s Sky Solar Holdings Co. to build 300 megawatts of
solar projects in the Andean country.  Empresa Nacional de Electricidad SA  (ENDESA CC) fell 0.8
percent to 827.98 pesos. Chile’s largest power generator said
yesterday it will appeal a decision by environmental authorities
that rejected its 740-megawatt Punta Alcalde thermoelectric
power project.  To contact the reporters on this story:
